  "text": "Although several novel chemotherapeutic compounds, including nab-paclitaxel and liposomal irinotecan, and chemotherapy regimens, such as FOLFIRINOX, have been successfully tested in clinical trials as conventional treatment options [CITATION_1] , the prognosis remains poor [CITATION_2] . To improve the prognosis of pancreatic cancer, the number of basic researches and clinical trials are increasing [CITATION_3] . In addition, the comprehensive precision medicine tools for therapeutic options that have been implemented in both the community and academic areas [CITATION_4] have led to better progression-free survival rates in patients receiving matched therapy.",
